Understanding units
- px
- % = according to parent depend krta hai
- vw, vh: vw stands for 'viewport width' and vh stands for 'viewport height' = according to screensize depend krta hai
vw and vh ka eik drawback: eik waqt pe jaakr ye bht zaada hi chota krdeta hai that's why now we learn vmax and vmin 
- vmax, vmin = vmax means 'jo bhi viewport maximum hai' and vmin means 'jo bhi viewport minimum hai'
Aksar media queries likhte waqt bht saare elements ko eik saath chota krna hota hai jo kaafi mushkil hojaata hai uske liye aata hai em and rem
- em, rem = em means 'parent ke font-size pr dependent' and rem means 'root element ke font-size pr dependent' which is approximately 16px so 1 rem = 16px.

